[+1196] The Trollstigen Looks Like a Hell of a Drive [PHOTO]
item.description: Trollstigen (English: The Troll Ladder) is a mountain road in Rauma, Norway, part of Norwegian National Road 63 connecting Åndalsnes in Rauma and Valldal in Norddal. It is a popular tourist attraction due to its steep incline of 9% and eleven hairpin bends up a steep mountain side. Vehicles over 12.4 meters long are prohibited from driving the road
